1.4.1fxi:
- circle ship radius reduced from 10 to 9 to reduce ship wall hits during
  ballruns
- support for fastradar packet (protocol version 0x4401)
- sendselfitems removed, server does not send any items to clients
- don't send pause icons to clients, clients know from 'mychar' whether
  someone pauses
- fixed rank ball cash amount for team cashed balls
- improved swapping code from Marcus Sundberg's rank1 patch
- a joining or unpausing player must always waiting for next round
- refactor some code (thanks Piotr Kamisinski)

1.4.0fxi:
- added /addr command
- serverHost option fix by Ben Armstrong
- minimum possible player turnspeed is now 0.1 (previously 4.0)
- patch to get rid of turnloss near walls and ships getting stuck in walls,
  including an /oldturn command can be used by individual players to use the
  old behaviour

1.3.8fxi:
- removed xpilot 4.3 based client again
- do not look for X in configure
	
1.3.7fxi:
- put back xpilot 4.3 based client
- fix keyboard turning speed to be invariant of fps
- fix delays in netserver.c: previously delays were too slow if fps was high,
  causing player timeouts
	
1.3.6fxi:
- removed xpilot 4.3 based client
- if client maxfps is 20, treat that as maxfps 254,
  this will make life easier for players with legacy clients
- same set of robots always to make aimers tests less random
  R0 = Cobra, R1 = Cobra, R2 = Uzi, R3 = Uzi
- removed feature that shooting can be done in intermediate frames
- set usewreckage option to false by default; we dont want wreckages
  usually, not at least on laggy servers to add more noise to steering
- removed a lot of server options
- in Punish_team and Team_game_over, don't require waiting players to have
  0 points to ignore them
	
1.3.5fxi:
- gameSpeed option for development purposes,
  option intGameSpeed is used for integer delays
- fixed bugs in object position calculations that could make server crash
- radar dot of locked player now blinks slowly also at high fps
- removed unused visibility array to save some memory
- removed the noQuit option
- removed score multipliers and options related to them
- removed some unnecessary balloptions
- added a feature: shooting can be done in intermediate frames too
	
1.3.4fxi:
- took away Mara turnqueue, after more testing it was agreed that its more 
  harmful than useful
- include string.h in rank.c
- took away shots from rank, fixed a bug losing a ball twice in rank
- show paused players to meta server, because paused players might be
  waiting for other players to join (thanks for the idea Kevin)
- add greeting string option, the greeting will show up for joining players
- changed option internalfps to fps
- changed startscripts to reflect changes in options (internalfps->fps)
  and fixed a bug in one script
- fixed the frame update in maxfps (taken from bp1)

1.3.3fxi:
- updates for ship turning comes at client frame rate (accidentally turned
  off this feature from earlier releases to check that the steering indeed
  behaves well at lower update rate, and does not have too much feeling 
  for loss)
- 800 start fuel as a test

1.3.2fxi:
- fixed the configure.ac script for FreeBSD to find expat library if 
  system keeps it installed in a non-standard place
- fixed the walls with Virus' turnqueue hack (should work better now
  with no steering loss)
- fixed rank to save scores when player exits
- fixed the treasure bug which was the result of the popping fix of 1.3.1
- fixed the limited rounds game to work; ugly hacks in 4.3.0 code was
  removed and cleaned up somewhat
- added xpping utility under contrib, not finished
- kps fix for server crash when someone quits (fxi-fix.diff)
- fixed the "loss in steering" bug (this improvement still needs rethinking)
- (still keeping maxballconnectorratio as 0.32, even though steering loss
  has been fixed, I think this is much better than the original 0.30, because 
  it allows for faster playing also when grabbing ball and releasing it, so 
  high speed manouvers with ball is more likely to succeed)
	
1.3.1fxi:
- encountered the first sync bug, so made the packet handling a critical
  section with other signals blocked; this improves packet handling, but
  will make scheduling frame updates slightly less accurate; the overall
  effect is still better steering
- fixed a 4.3.0 bug: the ball is now popped when hit with shields up
- fixed a timing bug; the pause player time was too short so it would
  pause one of the two players crashing into each other in some cases
- connector maxratio was increased from 0.30 to 0.32, because the ship
  moves on the average faster than before, so to support faster moves
  the connector must not snap as easily as before; this will not make
  records for ballruns faster though, but only ballruns on the average 
  will be faster
- fixed the ballpopping, it now shows correctly also on interpolated frames
- fixed the viewing, works now to view all players
- fixed a bug from 1.2.2: the shots routine can cause a server crash if the
  shots appear outside the map area
	
1.3.0fxi:
- much better packet handling
- "fxi" stands now for "Fast eXperimental Interpolation", the so called 
  interpolation method is now a well established method, so the 
  "eXperimental" from that part is removed. But "fast" comes from the new
  packet & mainloop handling, and it is "eXperimental". The new method
  is truly concurrent, with both its pros & cons. The advantage being that
  the server consumes still very little cpu but schedules better, and
  the disadvantage being that a concurrent program can cause alot 
  of problems. The concurrency correctness has not yet been verified!
- the ghost bullets just disappeared without any fixes to it. This problem 
  was not really easily fixable, and I was afraid that something like this 
  might happen. It would vanish as a side-effect from something else, which 
  again indicates that the code base is rather dirty.
- fixed the internalfps/framedivisor tuner to also reset frame_cycle 
  to synchronize server when changing rates; the server froze in some
  cases without this fix

1.2.2ix:
- deleted some unused code (shutdowntime, delay, etc.)
- fixed the metaupdate; got broken in 1.2.1ix
- fixed turning to update turns at a rate specified by maxfps; checked
  also that synchronization works properly
- fixed the problem related to bad steering & shooting
- fixed the deadliest scoring 
- fixed the endroundreset when cashing and alone
- optimized heavily the shots routine (e.g. no shots on rank)
- new teamcup2.xp map, optimized to allow more ballruns	

1.2.1ix:
- fixed the frame ordering;
  Here's an example of the situation; 
  Server ifps = 50; fdiv = 4; real = real frame; int = interpolated frame;
  EOP = End of the frame shuffle period

  client = 50 rfps
  ____   ___   ___   ___ | ____
  real - int - int - int - real ...
  ----   ---   ---   --- | ----
  20ms	 20ms  20ms  20ms|  20ms
			EOP
  client = 25 rfps
  ____   ___ | ___   ___   ____
  real - int - real -int - real ...
  ----   --- | ---   ---   ----
  40ms   40ms| 40ms  40ms  40ms
 	    EOP

  client = 16 2/3 rfps
  ____   ___   ___ | ___   ____
  real - int - int - real- int ...
  ----   ---   --- | ---   ----
  60ms   60ms  60ms| 60ms  60ms
		  EOP

  client  = 12 1/2 rfps
  ---- | ----
  real - real .. 
  ---- | ----
  80ms |
      EOP
NOTE: 16 2/3 will not work with a simple computation, because of the 
unsymmetricity it introduces.. so don't use 16 2/3 fps on a 50 fps server!
- deleted some options: roundtime, servershutdowntime
	

1.2.0ix:
- lock is now removed when last player with operator status leaves,
  same feature as on ng
- client side turning updates per second follow client fps rate(note that 
  the /maxturnsps in xpilot-ng is broken!)
- major feature: ported ranking code from ng (use /stats and option 
  -rankFilename and -rankwebpage (NOTE: ANY decent bloods server has a 
  ranking); you MUST at least use -rankFilename. If possible, you should 
  also have a publicly available rankwebdirectory, and copy the html files 
  there *every month*. The rank is reset by deleting the rankfilename(s). 
  Failure to do all of the above correctly will at least result in a 
  small interest for your server.
- added back the audiorequest packet to maintain compatibility
  with clients using sound requests (this server does not support any sound)
- added startscripts directory for various scripts to start server.
  You should use
  startscripts/publicserver.sh 
  if you don't have other ideas on how to set up a public blood's server; 
  it creates a rankfile and rankwebfile (whose path should be changed to a
  public webdirectory in your system if possible).

1.1.1ix:
- fixed ball counter (objects now do not get broken in interpolated frames, if
  they hit a wall)
- fixed refuel connector from connecting to all visible fuel boxes(used own
  code, the default implementation was horrible).
- fixed shooting timing
- fixed the wallcollisions; in the collision code, collisions are done
  componentwise on ship velocity and with the absolute value of 
  velocity sqrt(vx^2 + vy^2). The absolute values wasn't corrected with the 
  speedfactor for interpolated frames, so the resulting bounces had too much 
  velocity in them. This was also never done correctly in xpilot-ng when it
  used the block walls code.
- fixed internalfps and framedivisor - can be set on runtime and has error
  checking.
- added mainlooptime 
- some minor code deletions (removed sensor computations)
	
1.1.0ix:
- the redundant hp for high performance is removed, and ix is used instead:
  "Interpolating eXperimental".
  Server now uses interpolated frames put in-between real frames. Currently
  no game events except for wallcollisions take effect in the interpolated
  frames. This means that both ship steering and ballhandling is identical
  to old server (connector doesn't snap now, because both the ship and ball
  doesn't glide around). This is a big step forward and now one can claim
  that the server is almost fully xpilot-4 compatible (except for 
  wallcollisions) for those who want low fps
- removed the sending of shots as radar objects; going through the object
  list takes a lot of cpu time, because of the sparks, so it should be 
  avoided.	

1.0.2hpx:
- timerresolution option removed; whoever implemented that must have had
  a weak understanding of how it affects gameplay(you get what you ask for,
  but the side effects are so serious that you wouldn't want it), and it's 
  harmful to use for Linux 2.6 anyway.

- the option fps has lost its original meaning; now its used as an internal
  timeunit for various timings in the game, but it has nothing to do with
  the frame rate. This allows for different timings in the game independent of
  internalfps, which is in contrast to xpilot-ng server, where gamespeed had
  to equal at fps or be lower.
- use option gameSpeed now instead of fps to change internal speed of timings,
  there is no option fps any longer, you should use internalFps instead.
	
1.0.1hpx:
- server runs internally at different fps;
  you have the following choices:
 internalfps = 100; framedivisor = 8 ; probably too high 
 internalfps = 50 ; framedivisor = 4 ; high rate with correct scheduling
 internalfps = 25 ; framedivisor = 2 ; medium rate with correct scheduling
 internalfps = 12 ; framedivisor = 1 ; plain 12 fps with incorrect scheduling
				       on systems with 100 ticks.
 defaults to 25/2
 internalfps takes partly the role of the fps of the old server, but it
 determines only frame rate and nothing else(doesn't affect timings, with
 proper framedivisors).
	
1.0.0hpx:
- xpilot-fix6 changes(see xpilot-4.3.0fix-rc6 package)
- inlining of crucial code(collision + packetscanf)
- configure script(ugly xmkmf is history)
- LOTS of code cleanups(removed cannons, sound, wormholes, items,
  extra weapons, autopilot, hoverpause, stupid options, recoil,
  gravity, turnthrust fuel)
- internally server runs faster when processing packets
- no high fps support(will be done later with an interpolation method,
  which differs fundamentally from the way xpilot-ng does it)
